<h3>What is a Business Model?</h3>
<p>A business model is how your company creates, delivers, and captures value. It answers: Who are your customers? What do you offer them? How do you reach them? How do you make money?</p>
<h3>The 10 Core Business Models</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Product sales</strong> — Sell a product once. Jumia, Apple, Shoprite.</li>
<li><strong>Subscription</strong> — Recurring fee for ongoing access. Netflix, Spotify, SaaS tools.</li>
<li><strong>Marketplace</strong> — Connect buyers and sellers, take commission. Airbnb, Uber, Fiverr.</li>
<li><strong>Freemium</strong> — Free basic tier, paid premium. Zoom, Dropbox, LinkedIn.</li>
<li><strong>Advertising</strong> — Free product, sell user attention. Facebook, Google, TikTok.</li>
<li><strong>Transaction fee</strong> — Charge per transaction. Flutterwave, Stripe, PayPal.</li>
<li><strong>Licensing</strong> — License intellectual property. Patents, franchises, software licences.</li>
<li><strong>Consulting/Service</strong> — Sell expertise and time. Law firms, agencies, accountants.</li>
<li><strong>Razor and blade</strong> — Base product cheap, profit on consumables. Printers and ink.</li>
<li><strong>Data monetisation</strong> — Collect data, sell insights. Credit bureaus, market research firms.</li>
</ol>
<h3>The Business Model Canvas</h3>
<p>Created by Alexander Osterwalder, this one-page tool maps your entire business across 9 blocks: Customer Segments, Value Propositions, Channels, Customer Relationships, Revenue Streams, Key Resources, Key Activities, Key Partners, and Cost Structure.</p>
<div class="template-box"><div class="template-title">&#128196; Template: Business Model Canvas (Simplified)</div><div class="template-body">CUSTOMER SEGMENTS: Who are your customers? ______________
VALUE PROPOSITION: What problem do you solve? ____________
CHANNELS: How do you reach customers? ___________________
CUSTOMER RELATIONSHIPS: How do you retain them? ________
REVENUE STREAMS: How do you make money? _______________
KEY RESOURCES: What do you need to deliver? _____________
KEY ACTIVITIES: What must you do every day? _____________
KEY PARTNERS: Who do you rely on? ______________________
COST STRUCTURE: What are your main costs? ______________</div></div>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>Business model</strong> — How a company creates, delivers, and captures value<br>
<strong>Freemium</strong> — Free basic version with paid premium features<br>
<strong>Recurring revenue</strong> — Predictable income that repeats (subscriptions)<br>
<strong>Business Model Canvas</strong> — One-page framework mapping all elements of a business model
