    <div class="lesson-header" onclick="toggleLesson(9)"><div class="lesson-num" id="lnum-9">09</div><div class="lesson-info"><div class="lesson-title">Building Your Team</div><div class="lesson-subtitle">Co-founders, hiring, culture, equity splits, vesting</div></div><div class="lesson-status" id="lstatus-9"><span class="lock-icon">&#128274;</span></div><div class="lesson-toggle" id="ltoggle-9">&#8964;</div></div>
    <div class="lesson-body" id="lbody-9">
<h3>Why Team Matters More Than Idea</h3>
<p>Investors often say they invest in teams, not ideas. A great team can pivot from a bad idea to a winning one. A bad team will ruin a great idea. The most important decision you make as a founder is who you build with.</p>
<h3>The Ideal Founding Team</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>The Hacker</strong> — Builds the product. The technical co-founder.</li>
<li><strong>The Hustler</strong> — Sells, markets, fundraises. The business co-founder.</li>
<li><strong>The Designer / Domain Expert</strong> — Understands the problem deeply from lived experience.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Equity Splits and Vesting</h3>
<ul>
<li>Equal 50/50 splits seem fair but cause decision deadlock</li>
<li>The founder who contributes full-time from day one deserves more</li>
<li><strong>Vesting schedules</strong> protect everyone: 4-year vest with 1-year cliff means someone must stay 1 year to earn any equity, then earns monthly over 3 more years</li>
<li>Leave 10-15% as an <strong>option pool</strong> for future key employees</li>
</ul>
<h3>Hiring and Culture</h3>
<p>Your first 10 hires define your culture. Hire slow, fire fast. Look for competence, cultural alignment, and commitment to mission — not just salary. Culture is not perks — it is how decisions get made when no one is watching. Document your values early and model them yourself.</p>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>Co-founder</strong> — A person who starts a company alongside you<br>
<strong>Equity</strong> — Ownership share in the company<br>
<strong>Vesting schedule</strong> — Timeline over which equity is earned<br>
<strong>Cliff</strong> — Period before any equity vests (typically 1 year)<br>
<strong>Option pool</strong> — Equity reserved for future employees
