<h3>Why Legal Matters Early</h3>
<p>Many founders delay legal work because it seems boring or expensive. This is a costly mistake. Poor legal foundations cause: co-founder disputes with no agreement, IP theft, investor walkouts from messy cap tables, and regulatory shutdowns.</p>
<h3>Company Structures in Nigeria</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Sole Trader / Business Name</strong> — Simplest, cheapest. You and business are legally the same. All liability is personal.</li>
<li><strong>Private Limited Company (Ltd)</strong> — Separate legal entity. Shareholders limited to their investment. Required by investors. Register with Corporate Affairs Commission (CAC).</li>
<li><strong>Public Limited Company (Plc)</strong> — Can sell shares to the public. For large businesses only.</li>
</ul>
<h3>CAC Registration in Nigeria</h3>
<p>Register online at cac.gov.ng. Requirements: company name search, Memorandum and Articles of Association, details of directors and shareholders. Cost: approximately ₦10,000–₦50,000 depending on share capital.</p>
<h3>Intellectual Property Types</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Trademark</strong> — Brand name, logo, tagline</li>
<li><strong>Patent</strong> — Inventions and innovations</li>
<li><strong>Copyright</strong> — Automatically protects original creative works (code, writing, music)</li>
<li><strong>Trade secret</strong> — Confidential business information (algorithms, customer lists)</li>
</ul>
<h3>Essential Contracts</h3>
<ul>
<li>Co-founder agreement — roles, equity, vesting, exit</li>
<li>Employment contracts — terms for staff</li>
<li>NDA — protects confidential information</li>
<li>Terms of Service and Privacy Policy — required if you collect personal data</li>
</ul>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>CAC</strong> — Corporate Affairs Commission: Nigeria's company registration body<br>
<strong>Limited liability</strong> — Shareholders cannot lose more than they invested<br>
<strong>NDA</strong> — Non-Disclosure Agreement: confidentiality contract<br>
<strong>IP</strong> — Intellectual Property: legal ownership of created works and inventions
