    <div class="lesson-header" onclick="toggleLesson(13)"><div class="lesson-num" id="lnum-13">13</div><div class="lesson-info"><div class="lesson-title">Marketing Fundamentals</div><div class="lesson-subtitle">4Ps, marketing funnel, channels, content marketing, SEO basics</div></div><div class="lesson-status" id="lstatus-13"><span class="lock-icon">&#128274;</span></div><div class="lesson-toggle" id="ltoggle-13">&#8964;</div></div>
    <div class="lesson-body" id="lbody-13">
<h3>What is Marketing?</h3>
<p>Marketing is the process of creating awareness, generating desire, and communicating value so that the right people find and choose your product or service. It is everything you do to connect your solution to the people who need it.</p>
<h3>The 4Ps of Marketing</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Product</strong> — What you are selling. Its features, quality, design, and packaging.</li>
<li><strong>Price</strong> — What you charge. Your pricing strategy, discounts, payment terms.</li>
<li><strong>Place</strong> — Where and how you sell. Online, physical, direct, through distributors.</li>
<li><strong>Promotion</strong> — How you communicate. Advertising, content, social media, PR, word of mouth.</li>
</ul>
<h3>The Marketing Funnel</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Awareness</strong> — They know you exist. Social media, SEO, ads, word of mouth.</li>
<li><strong>Interest</strong> — They are curious. Blog posts, videos, demos.</li>
<li><strong>Consideration</strong> — They are evaluating. Case studies, pricing pages, free trials.</li>
<li><strong>Conversion</strong> — They buy. Checkout, sales call, sign-up.</li>
<li><strong>Retention</strong> — They come back. Email, loyalty programmes, great service.</li>
<li><strong>Advocacy</strong> — They tell others. Referrals, reviews, testimonials.</li>
</ol>
<h3>Key Marketing Channels for African Startups</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>WhatsApp marketing</strong> — Direct, personal, highest open rates in Africa</li>
<li><strong>Social media</strong> — Instagram, Twitter/X, TikTok, Facebook — choose where your customer lives</li>
<li><strong>Content marketing</strong> — Educational content that attracts your target audience organically</li>
<li><strong>Referrals</strong> — Highest trust, lowest cost. Build a referral programme early.</li>
<li><strong>Partnerships</strong> — Distribute through organisations that already reach your customer</li>
<li><strong>SEO</strong> — Rank in Google for searches your customers make</li>
</ul>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>Marketing funnel</strong> — The journey from awareness to purchase and advocacy<br>
<strong>SEO</strong> — Search Engine Optimisation: improving visibility in search results<br>
<strong>CAC</strong> — Cost to acquire one paying customer<br>
<strong>Retention</strong> — Keeping existing customers engaged and returning<br>
<strong>Persona</strong> — Fictional representation of ideal customer based on real research
