    <div class="lesson-header" onclick="toggleLesson(14)"><div class="lesson-num" id="lnum-14">14</div><div class="lesson-info"><div class="lesson-title">Sales Fundamentals</div><div class="lesson-subtitle">The sales process, consultative selling, objections, closing, pipeline</div></div><div class="lesson-status" id="lstatus-14"><span class="lock-icon">&#128274;</span></div><div class="lesson-toggle" id="ltoggle-14">&#8964;</div></div>
    <div class="lesson-body" id="lbody-14">
<h3>Sales vs Marketing</h3>
<p>Marketing creates awareness and desire. Sales converts that desire into a purchase. Both are essential. As a founder, you must be able to sell — because no one will sell your vision better than you, especially in the early days.</p>
<h3>The Sales Process</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Prospecting</strong> — Identifying potential customers who match your ideal customer profile</li>
<li><strong>Qualification</strong> — Confirming they have the problem, budget, authority, and need (BANT)</li>
<li><strong>Discovery</strong> — Deep conversation to understand their specific situation and pain</li>
<li><strong>Presentation</strong> — Demonstrating how your solution addresses their specific situation</li>
<li><strong>Handling objections</strong> — Addressing concerns with evidence and empathy</li>
<li><strong>Closing</strong> — Asking for and securing the commitment</li>
<li><strong>Follow-up</strong> — Delivering on promises, checking in, seeking referrals</li>
</ol>
<h3>Consultative Selling</h3>
<p>The most effective sales approach, especially for complex B2B products. Instead of pitching features, you ask questions to understand the customer's world deeply, then position your solution as the natural answer to their specific situation. You become a trusted advisor, not a vendor.</p>
<h3>Handling Objections</h3>
<p>Objections are not rejections — they are requests for more information. Common objections:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>"It is too expensive"</strong> — Quantify the cost of their current problem. Show ROI.</li>
<li><strong>"We are happy with our current solution"</strong> — Ask what they would improve if they could.</li>
<li><strong>"I need to think about it"</strong> — Understand what specifically they need to decide.</li>
<li><strong>"Now is not a good time"</strong> — Agree and schedule a specific follow-up date.</li>
</ul>
<div class="template-box"><div class="template-title">&#128196; Template: Sales Call Framework</div><div class="template-body">OPENING (2 min)
Build rapport. State the agenda. Confirm time available.

DISCOVERY (10-15 min)
"Tell me about how you currently handle [problem]."
"What does that cost you in time or money?"
"What happens if this is not fixed in 6 months?"

PRESENTATION (5-10 min)
"Based on what you have told me, here is how we solve that..."
[Tie every feature to their specific situation]

CLOSE (2-5 min)
"Does this solve the challenge you described?"
"What would need to be true for you to move forward today?"</div></div>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>Sales pipeline</strong> — Visual tracker of all prospects at different deal stages<br>
<strong>BANT</strong> — Budget, Authority, Need, Timeline — the four qualification criteria<br>
<strong>Consultative selling</strong> — Deep question-based selling that positions you as advisor<br>
<strong>ARR</strong> — Annual Recurring Revenue: predictable yearly revenue
