    <div class="lesson-header" onclick="toggleLesson(17)"><div class="lesson-num" id="lnum-17">17</div><div class="lesson-info"><div class="lesson-title">Digital Marketing and Growth Hacking</div><div class="lesson-subtitle">AARRR, viral loops, SEO, email, referrals, A/B testing</div></div><div class="lesson-status" id="lstatus-17"><span class="lock-icon">&#128274;</span></div><div class="lesson-toggle" id="ltoggle-17">&#8964;</div></div>
    <div class="lesson-body" id="lbody-17">
<h3>Growth Hacking</h3>
<p>Growth hacking is the use of creative, rapid, data-driven experiments across marketing, product, and operations to find the most efficient ways to grow. The term was coined by Sean Ellis in 2010. Famous examples: Hotmail added "PS: Get your free email at Hotmail" to every email sent. Dropbox offered free storage for referrals. Both grew explosively with minimal spend.</p>
<h3>The AARRR Pirate Metrics Framework</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Acquisition</strong> — How do users find you? (SEO, social, ads, referrals)</li>
<li><strong>Activation</strong> — Do they have a great first experience?</li>
<li><strong>Retention</strong> — Do they come back?</li>
<li><strong>Revenue</strong> — Do they pay?</li>
<li><strong>Referral</strong> — Do they tell others?</li>
</ul>
<h3>Key Digital Marketing Channels</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>SEO</strong> — Rank in Google for keywords your customers search. Long-term, compound growth.</li>
<li><strong>Social Media</strong> — Build audience and community. Instagram, Twitter/X, TikTok, LinkedIn depending on your audience.</li>
<li><strong>Email Marketing</strong> — Highest ROI of any digital channel (~$36-42 per $1 spent). Own your audience.</li>
<li><strong>WhatsApp</strong> — 95%+ open rates in Nigeria. Most direct channel to African customers.</li>
<li><strong>Paid Ads</strong> — Facebook/Instagram ads, Google ads. Fast but requires budget and testing.</li>
<li><strong>Content Marketing</strong> — YouTube, blogs, podcasts. Builds trust and attracts organic traffic.</li>
</ul>
<h3>The Viral Loop</h3>
<p>Design your product so that using it naturally leads to sharing it. Paystack's payment links are shared with customers who then discover Paystack. Zoom sends meeting invites that expose non-users to the product. Every share is free marketing.</p>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>Growth hacking</strong> — Creative data-driven experimentation to find efficient growth strategies<br>
<strong>AARRR</strong> — Acquisition, Activation, Retention, Revenue, Referral<br>
<strong>Viral coefficient (K)</strong> — Average new users each existing user brings<br>
<strong>A/B testing</strong> — Testing two versions to determine which performs better
