    <div class="lesson-header" onclick="toggleLesson(19)"><div class="lesson-num" id="lnum-19">19</div><div class="lesson-info"><div class="lesson-title">Customer Retention and Loyalty</div><div class="lesson-subtitle">Churn, NPS, LTV, loyalty programmes, onboarding, re-engagement</div></div><div class="lesson-status" id="lstatus-19"><span class="lock-icon">&#128274;</span></div><div class="lesson-toggle" id="ltoggle-19">&#8964;</div></div>
    <div class="lesson-body" id="lbody-19">
<h3>Why Retention Matters More Than You Think</h3>
<p>Most founders obsess over acquiring new customers. But research shows acquiring a new customer costs 5 to 25 times more than retaining an existing one. A 5% increase in retention can increase profits by 25% to 95%. The customers you already have are your most valuable asset.</p>
<h3>Measuring Retention</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Churn rate</strong> — Percentage of customers who leave in a period. Monthly churn of 10% means you lose 10 out of every 100 customers each month.</li>
<li><strong>Retention rate</strong> — 1 minus churn rate. 10% churn = 90% retention.</li>
<li><strong>LTV (Lifetime Value)</strong> — Total revenue from one customer over their entire relationship. Higher retention = higher LTV.</li>
<li><strong>NPS (Net Promoter Score)</strong> — Ask: "How likely are you to recommend us to a friend?" Scale 0-10. 9-10 = Promoters. 7-8 = Passives. 0-6 = Detractors. NPS = % Promoters - % Detractors.</li>
<li><strong>CSAT</strong> — Customer Satisfaction Score at specific interaction points.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Strategies to Improve Retention</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Onboarding experience</strong> — The first 7 days determine if a customer stays. Build a clear path to their first success.</li>
<li><strong>Proactive customer success</strong> — Contact customers before they have a problem. Check how they are doing.</li>
<li><strong>Loyalty programmes</strong> — Reward repeat behaviour. Points, exclusive access, early features.</li>
<li><strong>Community</strong> — Customers who connect with each other stay longer. Build a WhatsApp group, Facebook community, or Discord.</li>
<li><strong>Regular value delivery</strong> — Keep improving the product. Each update is a reason to stay.</li>
<li><strong>Exit interviews</strong> — When someone churns, call them and ask why. This data is gold.</li>
</ul>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>Churn rate</strong> — Percentage of customers lost in a given period<br>
<strong>NPS</strong> — Net Promoter Score: likelihood to recommend on -100 to +100 scale<br>
<strong>CSAT</strong> — Customer Satisfaction Score at specific moments<br>
<strong>Onboarding</strong> — The process of guiding a new customer to their first success
