    <div class="lesson-header" onclick="toggleLesson(20)"><div class="lesson-num" id="lnum-20">20</div><div class="lesson-info"><div class="lesson-title">Operations and Execution</div><div class="lesson-subtitle">SOPs, OKRs, KPIs, delegation, systems, working ON the business</div></div><div class="lesson-status" id="lstatus-20"><span class="lock-icon">&#128274;</span></div><div class="lesson-toggle" id="ltoggle-20">&#8964;</div></div>
    <div class="lesson-body" id="lbody-20">
<h3>Why Operations Matter</h3>
<p>Strategy without execution is just a dream. Operations is how your startup delivers value consistently, scales without breaking, and builds the systems that free the founder from doing everything manually. Most startups fail not from bad ideas but from poor execution and operational chaos.</p>
<h3>Key Operational Concepts</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>SOPs (Standard Operating Procedures)</strong> — Documented steps for any repeatable task. Writing is painful. The team doing tasks differently every time is more painful.</li>
<li><strong>OKRs (Objectives and Key Results)</strong> — A goal-setting framework used by Google, Spotify, and most high-performing teams. Objective: what you want to achieve. Key Results: 3-5 measurable milestones that confirm you achieved it.</li>
<li><strong>KPIs (Key Performance Indicators)</strong> — The handful of metrics that tell you if the business is healthy. Choose 3-5 maximum. Review weekly.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Working ON vs IN the Business</h3>
<p>Michael Gerber (E-Myth Revisited) identified the trap most small business owners fall into: they spend all their time doing the work rather than building the systems that do the work. The goal is to build a business that can operate without your constant presence.</p>
<h3>Delegation and Systems</h3>
<ul>
<li>Document a task before delegating it</li>
<li>Delegate outcomes, not just tasks — give context and authority</li>
<li>Build checklists, templates, and workflows that anyone can follow</li>
<li>Review but do not micromanage — trust + verification</li>
</ul>
<h3>OKR Example</h3>
<p><strong>Objective:</strong> Build a loyal customer base in Lagos this quarter.<br>
<strong>KR1:</strong> Acquire 500 paying customers by end of quarter.<br>
<strong>KR2:</strong> Achieve NPS of 50+.<br>
<strong>KR3:</strong> Keep monthly churn below 5%.</p>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>SOP</strong> — Standard Operating Procedure: documented steps for repeatable tasks<br>
<strong>OKR</strong> — Objectives and Key Results: strategic goal-setting framework<br>
<strong>KPI</strong> — Key Performance Indicator: metric showing goal achievement<br>
<strong>Bottleneck</strong> — The constraint limiting overall system throughput
</div><div class="quiz-container" id="quiz-20"><div class="quiz-header"><div class="quiz-header-top"><div class="quiz-icon">&#128203;</div><div class="quiz-title-wrap"><div class="quiz-eyebrow">// Topic Test &middot; Lesson 20</div><div class="quiz-title">Lesson 20 Assessment</div></div></div><div class="quiz-meta-row"><div class="quiz-badge">10 Questions</div><div class="quiz-pass-badge">&#9889; Pass Mark: 60%</div><div class="quiz-timer">&#9201; <span id="qtimer-20">0s</span></div></div></div><div class="quiz-questions" id="qq-20"><div class="quiz-q" id="q-20-0"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q1</span>What is operations in a startup context?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,0,0,1)">The office location</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,0,1,1)">All the systems, processes, and activities that deliver value to customers consistently</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,0,2,1)">The accounting department</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,0,3,1)">Investor relations</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-20-0"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-20-1"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q2</span>What is an SOP?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,1,0,1)">Start of Production</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,1,1,1)">Standard Operating Procedure: documented steps for completing a repeatable task consistently</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,1,2,1)">Statement of Performance</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,1,3,1)">Senior Operations Position</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-20-1"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-20-2"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q3</span>What is OKR?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,2,0,1)">Operating Key Requirement</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,2,1,1)">Objectives and Key Results: a goal-setting framework</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,2,2,1)">Online Knowledge Repository</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,2,3,1)">Operations and Key Revenue</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-20-2"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-20-3"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q4</span>What does 'working ON the business vs IN the business' mean?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,3,0,1)">There is no difference</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,3,1,1)">Working in the business means doing daily tasks; working on the business means improving strategy, systems, and future direction</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,3,2,1)">Working on means physical office work</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,3,3,1)">Working in means managing remote teams</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-20-3"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-20-4"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q5</span>What is a KPI?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,4,0,1)">Kenya Payments Institution</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,4,1,1)">Key Performance Indicator: a measurable value showing how effectively a goal is being achieved</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,4,2,1)">Knowledge Process Infrastructure</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,4,3,1)">Key Partner Integration</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-20-4"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-20-5"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q6</span>What is bottleneck in business operations?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,5,0,1)">A type of company structure</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,20,5,1,1)">The constraint or slowest step