  <div class="module-header">&#127775; Module 4 &mdash; Scaling and Advanced Strategy (Lessons 21&ndash;25)</div>
  <div class="lesson-card locked" id="lcard-21" data-lesson="21"><div class="lesson-header" onclick="toggleLesson(21)"><div class="lesson-num" id="lnum-21">21</div><div class="lesson-info"><div class="lesson-title">Pitching to Investors</div><div class="lesson-subtitle">Pitch deck, elevator pitch, valuations, SAFE, convertible notes</div></div><div class="lesson-status" id="lstatus-21"><span class="lock-icon">&#128274;</span></div><div class="lesson-toggle" id="ltoggle-21">&#8964;</div></div><div class="lesson-body" id="lbody-21"><h3>Why Fundraising is a Skill</h3>
<p>Raising from investors requires storytelling, financial literacy, and the ability to handle rejection. The best time to raise is when you have momentum — not when you are desperate.</p>
<h3>The 11-Slide Pitch Deck</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Company purpose</strong> — One sentence: what you do and for whom</li>
<li><strong>Problem</strong> — The pain you solve. Make investors feel it.</li>
<li><strong>Solution</strong> — Your product and why it works</li>
<li><strong>Market size</strong> — TAM, SAM, SOM with credible numbers</li>
<li><strong>Business model</strong> — How you make money</li>
<li><strong>Traction</strong> — Revenue, users, growth rate — proof it is working</li>
<li><strong>Go-to-market</strong> — How you acquire customers at scale</li>
<li><strong>Competition</strong> — The landscape and your differentiation</li>
<li><strong>Team</strong> — Why you are the right people for this problem</li>
<li><strong>Financials</strong> — 3-year projections and use of funds</li>
<li><strong>The Ask</strong> — How much, at what valuation, for what milestones</li>
</ol>
<h3>Funding Instruments</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Equity round</strong> — Investors receive shares at agreed pre-money valuation</li>
<li><strong>Convertible note</strong> — A loan that converts to equity at next round, usually at 15-25% discount</li>
<li><strong>SAFE (Simple Agreement for Future Equity)</strong> — Y Combinator's instrument. No interest or maturity date. Simplest early-stage structure.</li>
</ul>
<div class="template-box"><div class="template-title">&#128196; Template: Elevator Pitch Formula</div><div class="template-body">Hi, I am [name], co-founder of [company].

We help [target customer] who struggle with [specific problem].

Our product [solution] achieves [key benefit].

We have [traction] in [time period].

We are raising [amount] to reach [specific milestone].

Are you open to a 20-minute conversation?</div></div>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>Pitch deck</strong> — Visual investor presentation (10-15 slides)<br>
<strong>Pre-money valuation</strong> — Company value before the investment round<br>
<strong>SAFE</strong> — Simple Agreement for Future Equity<br>
<strong>Dilution</strong> — Reduction in ownership % when new shares are issued
