tors bet on teams — they need to believe you can execute this specific vision</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,2,2,1)">It is the first slide</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,2,3,1)">Legal requirement</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-21-2"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-21-3"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q4</span>What is a SAFE?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,3,0,1)">A bank savings product</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,3,1,1)">Simple Agreement for Future Equity — converts to shares at next round</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,3,2,1)">A security certificate</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,3,3,1)">A loan with interest</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-21-3"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-21-4"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q5</span>What does a convertible note offer?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,4,0,1)">Free equity with no strings</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,4,1,1)">A loan that converts to equity at the next round usually with a discount</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,4,2,1)">A government subsidy</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,4,3,1)">A fixed interest bond</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-21-4"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-21-5"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q6</span>What is the purpose of the Ask slide?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,5,0,1)">To show off your team</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,5,1,1)">To state how much you are raising, at what valuation, and for what milestones</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,5,2,1)">To list your products</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,5,3,1)">To thank investors</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-21-5"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-21-6"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q7</span>What makes traction the most convincing slide?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,6,0,1)">It has the best design</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,6,1,1)">It shows real evidence the market wants your product — revenue, users, growth rate</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,6,2,1)">It comes first</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,6,3,1)">It lists investors</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-21-6"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-21-7"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q8</span>What is the elevator pitch?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,7,0,1)">A 30-minute detailed presentation</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,7,1,1)">A 30-90 second compelling summary of your business</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,7,2,1)">A written document</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,7,3,1)">An email to investors</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-21-7"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-21-8"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q9</span>What is dilution?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,8,0,1)">Reducing product quality</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,8,1,1)">Reduction in existing ownership percentage when new shares are issued</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,8,2,1)">Lowering your price</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,8,3,1)">Weakening your brand</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-21-8"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-21-9"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q10</span>Why should founders avoid raising money when desperate?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,9,0,1)">Desperation is a sign of failure</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,9,1,1)">Desperation destroys negotiating power and leads to accepting unfair terms</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,9,2,1)">Investors can smell it</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,21,9,3,1)">It is not a real concern</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-21-9"></div></div></div><div class="quiz-actions"><span class="quiz-answered-count" id="qcount-21"><span>0</span>/10 answered</span><button class="quiz-submit-btn" id="qsub-21" onclick="submitQuiz(21)" disabled>Submit Test &#8594;</button></div><div class="quiz-result" id="qres-21" style="display:none"></div></div></div></div>

  <div class="lesson-card locked" id="lcard-22" data-lesson="22"><div class="lesson-header" onclick="toggleLesson(22)"><div class="lesson-num" id="lnum-22">22</div><div class="lesson-info"><div class="lesson-title">Scaling Your Business</div><div class="lesson-subtitle">Growing vs scaling, levers, network effects, product-led growth, GTM</div></div><div class="lesson-status" id="lstatus-22"><span class="lock-icon">&#128274;</span></div><div class="lesson-toggle" id="ltoggle-22">&#8964;</div></div><div class="lesson-body" id="lbody-22"><h3>Growing vs Scaling</h3>
<p>Growth adds inputs proportionally to outputs — hire 2x people to serve 2x customers. Scaling grows revenue much faster than costs — serve 10x customers without 10x costs. Technology enables scaling. Most traditional businesses grow. Tech-enabled businesses scale.</p>
<h3>The 6 Scaling Levers</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Technology and automation</strong> — Software, AI, and bots replace manual work at scale</li>
<li><strong>Network effects</strong> — Each new user makes the product more valuable for all users (WhatsApp, Uber, marketplaces)</li>
<li><strong>Brand</strong> — A trusted brand attracts customers without proportional marketing spend</li>
<li><strong>Distribution partnerships</strong> — Others sell your product (agents, resellers, app stores)</li>
<li><strong>Franchise/licensing</strong> — Others operate under your systems and brand</li>
<li><strong>Data flywheel</strong> — More users generate data that improves the product, attracting more users</li>
</ol>
<h3>Growth Motions</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Product-led growth (PLG)</strong> — Product drives acquisition, activation, expansion. Dropbox, Notion, Zoom.</li>
<li><strong>Sales-led growth</strong> — Sales team drives growth. Enterprise software.</li>
<li><strong>Marketing-led growth</strong> — Brand and content drive growth. Consumer brands.</li>
<li><strong>Community-led growth</strong> — Community drives acquisition. Discord, Notion, Figma.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Are You Ready to Scale?</h3>
<p>You are ready when: PMF is proven (40%+ NPS), you have a repeatable acquisition channel, unit economics are healthy (LTV:CAC 3:1+), and your team and systems can handle 10x volume without breaking.</p>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>Network effect</strong> — Product becomes more valuable as more people use it<br>
<strong>Product-led growth</strong> — Growth driven by the product experience itself<br>
<strong>Data flywheel</strong> — More data improves the product which attracts more users<br>
<strong>Go-to-market</strong> — Strategy for reaching and converting customers at scale
