  <div class="lesson-card locked" id="lcard-29" data-lesson="29"><div class="lesson-header" onclick="toggleLesson(29)"><div class="lesson-num" id="lnum-29">29</div><div class="lesson-info"><div class="lesson-title">Building in Public and Personal Branding</div><div class="lesson-subtitle">Sharing your journey, thought leadership, newsletters, Twitter/X, LinkedIn</div></div><div class="lesson-status" id="lstatus-29"><span class="lock-icon">&#128274;</span></div><div class="lesson-toggle" id="ltoggle-29">&#8964;</div></div><div class="lesson-body" id="lbody-29"><h3>Building in Public — The New Competitive Advantage</h3>
<p>Building in public means sharing your startup journey openly — the progress, the failures, the lessons, the real numbers. What was once considered risky has become one of the most powerful growth strategies of the internet era.</p>
<h3>Why Build in Public?</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Early customers</strong> — People become invested in your journey before you launch. First customers are waiting when you do.</li>
<li><strong>Investor discovery</strong> — Investors discover founders who document their journey. Several significant investments started from a single honest tweet.</li>
<li><strong>Talent attraction</strong> — The best people want to work for founders they have followed, believe in, and respect.</li>
<li><strong>Accountability</strong> — Stating goals publicly creates powerful commitment pressure.</li>
<li><strong>Community before product</strong> — You build an audience before you have a product. When you launch, people already care.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Platforms and What to Share</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Twitter/X</strong> — Real-time updates, quick lessons, connecting with investors and founders globally</li>
<li><strong>LinkedIn</strong> — Professional audience, best for B2B founders, longer thought leadership posts</li>
<li><strong>Newsletter</strong> — Your most valuable channel. You own the email list — no algorithm can take it away.</li>
<li><strong>YouTube</strong> — Documentary-style journey videos for maximum engagement</li>
</ul>
<h3>What to Share Weekly</h3>
<ul>
<li>Real metrics with context (revenue, users, churn) — not just the wins</li>
<li>What you tried and what failed — the honest lessons are gold</li>
<li>Decision frameworks and how you think about hard problems</li>
<li>Industry insights and original perspectives on your market</li>
</ul>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>Building in public</strong> — Sharing your startup journey openly as you build<br>
<strong>Thought leadership</strong> — Consistent expert insight sharing that builds authority<br>
<strong>Newsletter</strong> — Owned email channel that bypasses platform algorithms<br>
<strong>Personal brand</strong> — Public reputation built through consistent content and expertise
