  <div class="lesson-card locked" id="lcard-30" data-lesson="30"><div class="lesson-header" onclick="toggleLesson(30)"><div class="lesson-num" id="lnum-30">30</div><div class="lesson-info"><div class="lesson-title">Your 90-Day Launch Plan</div><div class="lesson-subtitle">Validate, build, launch — your structured roadmap from student to founder</div></div><div class="lesson-status" id="lstatus-30"><span class="lock-icon">&#128274;</span></div><div class="lesson-toggle" id="ltoggle-30">&#8964;</div></div><div class="lesson-body" id="lbody-30"><h3>The End is the Beginning</h3>
<p>This is the final lesson of 30. Everything you have learned — opportunity identification, customer discovery, business models, finance, marketing, legal, team building, pitching, scaling, and resilience — has prepared you for one thing: <strong>action</strong>. Knowledge without execution is just potential. The 90-day plan is your bridge.</p>
<h3>Phase 1: Validate (Days 1-30)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Week 1 — Write your problem hypothesis and target customer profile clearly</li>
<li>Week 2 — Conduct 10 customer discovery interviews (use the interview script from Lesson 3)</li>
<li>Week 3 — Analyse findings. Does the problem exist? Will they pay? Pivot or proceed.</li>
<li>Week 4 — Build and launch a smoke test. Aim for 10+ sign-ups or 1 pre-order.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Phase 2: Build (Days 31-60)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Week 5-6 — Build your MVP. Use no-code if technical resources are limited.</li>
<li>Week 7 — Give access to 5-10 beta users. Observe. Ask. Do not pitch — listen.</li>
<li>Week 8 — Refine based on feedback. Fix the biggest friction point. Prepare for launch.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Phase 3: Launch and Grow (Days 61-90)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Week 9-10 — Public launch. Activate every network, community, and channel you have.</li>
<li>Week 11 — Analyse the data. What is working? Double down. What is not? Stop or fix it.</li>
<li>Week 12 — Set your next 90-day goals. Consider funding if growth metrics justify it.</li>
</ul>
